      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(otel): set logBodies=true in default content capture policy",
        "body": "Closes #95633\n\n## Summary\n\nOTLP log bodies were always captured when content capture was enabled via boolean `diagnostics.otel.captureContent: true`, but the object-form config ignored `logBodies` and the Zod schema rejected it entirely. Two fixes:\n\n1. **Schema**: Add `logBodies` to the object-form `captureContent` Zod schema so users can explicitly opt in.\n2. **Resolution**: `resolveContentCapturePolicy` now reads `config.logBodies` instead of hardcoding `false`, so explicit `logBodies: true` is respected.\n\n`NO_CONTENT_CAPTURE` (the fallback when no config is provided) keeps `logBodies: false` — it is documented as no-content-capture and must not flip that default.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n# The config schema now accepts logBodies\ndiagnostics.otel.captureContent.logBodies → z.boolean().optional() in Zod schema\ndiagnostics.otel.captureContent.logBodies → labeled in schema.labels.ts\ndiagnostics.otel.captureContent.logBodies → documented in schema.help.ts\n\n# Before: object-form { enabled: true, logBodies: true } was stripped by .strict()\n# After:  logBodies is a recognized key and passed through to the policy\n```\n\n**Not tested:** End-to-end with a live OTLP collector.",
